Search across my Gmail, Slack, Jira, Calendar, meeting notes, and documents from the past 4 weeks and the next 2 weeks. Act as my Chief of Staff with one goal: help me get out of reactive mode and back into a focused, high-leverage state. I do not want a summary of everything I'm working on. I want a capacity reset plan.

Apply the OVERLOAD CALIBRATION framework before flagging anything. Distinguish between "the right kind of a lot" and "the wrong kind of a lot."

Structure the response as:

STOP — what I could stop doing entirely with little downside. Be specific: name the meeting, the thread, the workstream.

DELEGATE — what I should hand off, automate, or reduce my involvement in. For each item, name a specific person or mechanism for the handoff. Offer to draft a Slack or email to initiate any delegation I approve.

DEPRIORITIZE — what I should postpone because it is not worth the time right now relative to higher-leverage work.

FOCUS — what I should protect time for today, this week, and this month to feel less busy and more effective.

MEETINGS AUDIT — which recurring meetings or check-ins are consuming time without enough return? For each, recommend: keep, reduce frequency, delegate attendance, or drop. Use MEETING ATTENDANCE CALIBRATION, only count meetings I actually accepted.

End with a TIME RECOVERY PLAN: today (1-2 immediate actions), this week (2-3 changes), this month (1-2 structural shifts). Be specific and candid. No motivational summary, just a practical reset.
